\sin 49^\circ = \frac{h-5.5}{43\ {\rm ft}}.
\] Solving for $h$ gives $h = 43\ {\rm ft}\cdot \sin 49^\circ + 5.5\ {\rm ft} \approx \boxed{38.56}$ feet.
</think>

The answer is $\boxed{38.56}$.

We first calculate the sample proportion, $\hat{p}$. There are $11$ "Yes" responses to a total of $20$ responses, so $\hat{p}=\frac{11}{20}=0.55$. Since the confidence level is $98.2\%$, the corresponding critical value is $z^*=2.39$ (you can look this up in a standard normal table, or use a calculator). Finally, we have the margin of error of $0.031$. Therefore, the sample size is \begin{align*} n &= \left(\frac{z^*}{\mbox{margin of error}}\right)^2 \hat{p}(1-\hat{p}) \\ &= \left(\frac{2.39}{0.031}\right)^2 (0.55)(1-0.55)\\ &\approx \boxed{1480}. \end{align*}
</think>

The answer is $\boxed{1480}$.

