We are given that $AB=14$ and $\angle CAB=49^\circ$, so we have \begin{align*}
\tan(\angle CAB)&=\frac{BC}{AB}\\
\Rightarrow\qquad \tan(49^\circ)&=\frac{BC}{14}\\
\Rightarrow\qquad BC&=14\times\tan(49^\circ)\\
\Rightarrow\qquad BC&\approx\boxed{15.07\text{ m}}.
\end{align*}
