Let $r$ be the radius of the circle through $B$ and $D$ that is tangent to $AC$ and let $O$ be the center of the circle. Then, $OB = OD = r$ and $\angle OBA = \angle ODA = 90^\circ$. Let $H$ be the foot of the perpendicular from $A$ to $BC$. Then $AH = 20 - 12 = 8$ and $BH = 15 - 9 = 6$. Let $K$ be the foot of the perpendicular from $O$ to $AC$. Then $OK = r$ and $HK = 8 - r$.

[asy]
