We have
\begin{align*}
\lim_{p \to 0+} \left( \int_{E} \! f^{p}(x) w(x) \, \mathrm{d} x \right)^{1/p}
&= \lim_{p \to 0+} \exp\left( \frac{1}{p} \ln \left( \int_{E} \! f^{p}(x) w(x) \, \mathrm{d} x \right) \right) \\
&= \exp\left( \lim_{p \to 0+} \frac{1}{p} \ln \left( \int_{E} \! f^{p}(x) w(x) \, \mathrm{d} x \right) \right) \\
&= \exp\left( \int_{E}^{w ( x ) \cdot\operatorname{l n}} f ( x ) \mathrm{d} x \right) \\
&= \boxed{\text{F}}.
\end{align*}
</think>

The answer is $\boxed{\text{F}}$.

