Recall that $\frac{a}{b} \cdot \frac{c}{d} = \frac{a \cdot c}{b \cdot d}$. Therefore, \begin{align*} \frac{16}{p^2} \cdot \frac{4 p^2 q^2}{p^4} \div \frac{8 p^4}{p^6} &= \frac{16}{p^2} \cdot \frac{4 p^2 q^2}{p^4} \cdot \frac{p^6}{8 p^4} \\ &= \frac{16 \cdot 4 p^2 q^2 \cdot p^6}{p^2 \cdot p^4 \cdot 8 p^4}. \end{align*} Cancel the common factors in the numerator and denominator to get \begin{align*} \frac{16 \cdot 4 p^2 q^2 \cdot p^6}{p^2 \cdot p^4 \cdot 8 p^4} &= \frac{2 \cdot 4 q^2 \cdot p^6}{1 \cdot 1 \cdot p^4} \\ &= \boxed{8 p^2 q^2}. \end{align*}
</think>

The answer is $\boxed{8 p^2 q^2}$.

