The centroid of the whole square is $O$. The centroid of triangle $AEB$ is $E$. Because the area of triangle $AEB$ is $1/3$ that of the square, we have $\overrightarrow{OG} = \frac{2}{3}\overrightarrow{OE}$. Since $\overrightarrow{OE} = \overrightarrow{OD} - \overrightarrow{DE}$, we have
$$\overrightarrow{OG} = \frac{2}{3}\left(\overrightarrow{OD} - \overrightarrow{DE}\right) = \frac{2}{3}\left(\frac{1}{2}\overrightarrow{OA} - \overrightarrow{DE}\right) = \frac{1}{3}\overrightarrow{OA} - \frac{2}{3}\overrightarrow{DE}.$$Hence, $x = \frac{2}{3}DE$. To find $DE$, we note that
$$\begin{aligned} \overrightarrow{DE} &= \overrightarrow{DO} + \overrightarrow{OE} \\ &= \frac{1}{2}\overrightarrow{DA} + \frac{2}{3}\overrightarrow{EG} \\ &= \frac{1}{2}\overrightarrow{DA} + \frac{2}{3}\left(\overrightarrow{OD} - \overrightarrow{OG}\right) \\ &= \frac{1}{2}\overrightarrow{DA} + \frac{2}{3}\overrightarrow{OD} - \frac{2}{3}\overrightarrow{OG} \\ &= \frac{1}{2}\overrightarrow{DA} + \frac{2}{3}\overrightarrow{OD} - \frac{2}{3}\cdot\frac{1}{3}\overrightarrow{OA} \\ &= \frac{1}{6}\overrightarrow{DA} + \frac{1}{3}\overrightarrow{OD}. \end{aligned}$$Therefore, $DE = \frac{1}{6}a + \frac{1}{3}x = \frac{1}{6}a + \frac{1}{9}a = \frac{5}{18}a$. Then $x = \frac{2}{3}DE = \frac{5}{27}a$. The distance from $E$ to $AD$ is $\frac{1}{2}a - x = \frac{7}{27}a \approx 0.259a$.

