The variance of a linear combination of random variables is given by: \begin{align*} Var(a_1X_1+a_2X_2+\dots+a_nX_n)&=a_1^2Var(X_1)+a_2^2Var(X_2)+\dots\\&\quad+a_n^2Var(X_n)\\&\quad+2a_1a_2Cov(X_1,X_2)+2a_1a_3Cov(X_1,X_3)\\&\quad+\dots+2a_{n-1}a_nCov(X_{n-1},X_n) \end{align*}
Thus, the variance of ${\hat\beta}_{9}-{\hat\beta}_{8}$ is: \begin{align*} Var({\hat\beta}_{9}-{\hat\beta}_{8})&=Var({\hat\beta}_{9})+Var({\hat\beta}_{8})\\&\quad-2Cov({\hat\beta}_{9},{\hat\beta}_{8})\\&=0.029926+0.017092-2(0.017092)\\&=0.009826 \end{align*}
The standard error is the square root of the variance, which is $\sqrt{0.009826}\approx 0.0991\approx \boxed{0.099}$.
