We first find the equation of the normal line. The parabola $y^2 = 2px$ has focus $\left(\frac{p}{2}, 0\right)$, so the normal line at $\left(\frac{p}{2}, p\right)$ has slope $-\frac{1}{p}$. Thus, the equation of the normal line is
\[y - p = -\frac{1}{p} \left(x - \frac{p}{2}\right),\]or $y = -\frac{1}{p} x + \frac{3}{2}$.

